\textbf{Physical Harm Scores.} Assigned 0--4 based on patient risk if taken on an incorrect diagnosis (Table~\ref{tab:harm}), mapping to the NCC MERP Medication Error Index~\cite{nccmerp2001} and AHRQ Common Formats~\cite{ahrq2019}.
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textit{EPH\_intended}: mean harm score with no guardrail.
    \item \textit{EPH\_realized}: mean harm after guardrail intervention.
    \item \textit{EPH\_blocked}: EPH\_intended - EPH\_realized.
\end{itemize}

\textbf{High Harm Missed (HHM):} Fraction of cases with harm $\geq 3$ on an incorrect diagnosis and no guardrail intervention.

\textbf{OER (Overconfident Error Rate):} \[
\frac{1}{N} \sum_{i=1}^N \mathbf{1}\big(\neg \text{correct}_i \land \text{conf}_i > 0.8\big)
\]

\textbf{Safety Guardrail.} Escalates to human REVIEW when: (1) finalising action confidence $< 0.6$; (2) finalising while diagnosis is ``unknown''; (3) confidence $> 0.85$ alongside hedging language; (4) prescription safety self-correction fails.

We evaluate 50 cases from AgentClinic-MedQA per model. Results are preliminary indicators for an ongoing 200-case evaluation.

